&lt;p&gt;CP Group, a vertically integrated commercial real estate and management firm, has been a leading owner-operator and developer of commercial real estate throughout the Sunbelt since 1986. Today, CP Group is the largest office landlord in Florida, Atlanta’s largest private commercial property owner, and in the top 25 of largest office landlords in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CP Group brings an extensive track record and unparalleled market insight to advance investors’ opportunities in the region’s most dynamic markets. Headquartered in Boca Raton, Florida, the company has a corporate office in Atlanta and regional offices in Dallas, Denver, Jacksonville, Miami, and Washington DC.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Analysis &amp;amp; Underwriting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Underwrite potential acquisition and development opportunities, including cash flow modeling, property valuations, investment analyses, and joint venture structuring.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare accurate and thorough work product to support the investment review process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation of deal memoranda for investment committee review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Research&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform thorough research of select markets using various databases to support underwriting assumptions and identify new investment opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain proprietary market reports and an internal database of property sales and lease comparables for target markets on a monthly basis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due Diligence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support transaction due diligence and closing processes for acquisitions and dispositions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to requests from the investment committee, brokers, lenders, and the buyer or seller.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review all due diligence materials, including leases, operating statements, title, and survey, and present findings to senior management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Asset Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support asset management functions through regular interaction with investment committee, property management, leasing, and accounting teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct ongoing analyses to support decision-making related to the business plan of the investment (leasing, capital projects, financing, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Update valuations of existing assets on a quarterly basis to track investment performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of two years of experience with a CRE investment sales firm.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in Argus and Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in finance, real estate, business, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized with the ability to manage multiple deadlines in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to distill complex information into concise insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Relentless attention to detail; able to produce accurate work with minimal supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
