&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CP Group, a vertically integrated commercial real estate and management firm, has been a leading owner-operator and developer of commercial real estate throughout the Sunbelt since 1986. Today, CP Group is the largest office landlord in Florida, Atlanta’s largest private commercial property owner, and in the top 25 of largest office landlords in the United States.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CP Group brings an extensive track record and unparalleled market insight to advance investors’ opportunities in the region’s most dynamic markets. Headquartered in Boca Raton, Florida, the company has a corporate office in Atlanta and regional offices in Dallas, Denver, Jacksonville, Miami, and Washington DC.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assistant Property Manager supports the management team of a commercial office property in areas including financial and lease administration, operations, tenant relations, vendor contract administration, construction project administration and tenant improvement management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assistant Property Manager also has organizational duties such as liaising with tenants, collecting rent, doing basic bookkeeping, organizing property tours and overseeing facility maintenance. You will also be responsible for evaluating service applicants and negotiating contracts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with tenant renewals, expansions and contractions including coordination of move-ins and move-outs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the development and administration of an operating budget and capital improvement budget for the property&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with monitoring expenses and operating within the parameters of the approved budgets and reporting/explaining variances accordingly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the daily financial management of the property with specific attention to accounts receivable, accounts payable, and all necessary financial records and files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with forecasting of income and expenses to ensure adequate cash flow and reserves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to review and comprehend operating expense reconciliations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lease Administration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with abstracting new leases and/or amendments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret lease documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer all tenant leases and assure compliance of lease provisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for timely collection of all rents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise Senior Property/Property Manager if rent delinquency response is required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with reconciling, billing, and collecting tenant escalations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for obtaining tenant insurance certificates&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface and maintain positive relationship with leasing agents and brokers as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist Property Manager with daily operations of the properties to assure quality standards are maintained; Perform regular inspections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct maintenance staff on maintenance programs relating to the condition and appearance of the property&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend and/or approve alterations and maintenance as necessary to Property Manager&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with developing and implementing a property manual including security and emergency policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with developing weekly/monthly updates, summaries and reports as required for property activities and tenant relations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;

